text: Paul Jones Fannin (January 29, 1907January 13, 2002) was an American businessman and politician. He was a Republican. He was a U.S. Senator from Arizona from 1965 to 1977. He was the 11th Governor of Arizona from 1959 to 1965. Fannin died of a stroke in Phoenix, Arizona on January 13, 2002 at the age of 94. ==References== Category:1907 births Category:2002 deaths Category:Arizona Republicans Category:Deaths from stroke Category:Governors of Arizona Category:United States senators from Arizona Category:Businesspeople from Kentucky Category:Businesspeople from Arizona Category:Politicians from Kentucky Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:People from Ashland, Kentucky
